name: SHS POISON COFFEE
address: Br Seseh, Singapadu, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
types: coffee_shop, vegan_restaurant, cafe, vegetarian_restaurant, indonesian_restaurant, restaurant, food, store
review 1:
Simple but delicious. If you love solitude, you will love it here. If you have been tired of luxuries and noise in a busy area, you will love it here.

Japanese manual brew tastes the same as in Japan.

Espresso Peach Squash smells super good, a little bit too sweet which you can tell the barista to reduce the sweetness a bit.

Matcha shake is yummy and perfect for the afternoon‚Äôs hot weather.

This place is small but great coffee quality

The service is fast.

There is a co-working space which is cool as well.
review 2: Beautiful and cozy mini cafe that gives you a rustic nostalgic vibes out of the hectic city. Good coffee and their food was delicious. Reasonable price. Moreover, a very friendly owner Mr.Rizky, gives plenty of place and food suggestions for tourist. Such a great place!
review 3:
She Poison Coffee is tucked away from the main road, but it's still relatively easy to find. The parking space is not very expansive, so if you're driving, you might need to look for alternative parking. The cafe itself is small but cozy, and the speed of food service is quite decent.

They have a small bookshelf, which adds a nice touch to the ambiance. As it's a cafe, the menu doesn't offer a wide variety of large meals, but it's perfect for a relaxed hangout. Moreover, there's a dedicated space for those who want to "Work from Cafe," and they provide Wi-Fi. The restroom is small but comfortable and clean, rounding up the experience.
review 4: A amazing cafe with chill vibes ! Great food and a fantastic coffee ü§óü§©ü§©ü§©ü§©ü§©ü§© thanks !
review 5: Cute little spot in a village. The food was tasty and prices reasonable but portions were a bit small. Coffee was nice. No complaints. Small indoor space was semi air conditioned and outside had smokers but it was not really busy so no problems. Will visit again.

review 1:
Indulged in the beef lawar and satai at this Balinese local spot, and I'm still savoring the incredible flavors. The beef lawar had the perfect blend of spices, and the satai was grilled to perfection ‚Äì juicy and flavorful.
The real showstopper was the serapah and its rawon, an absolute game-changer. Its unique taste elevated the entire meal, leaving a lasting impression. If you're a food enthusiast, this place is a haven for authentic Balinese culinary delights. Highly recommended!

I must say, this place serves the best authentic chicken lawar in Bali! I've been ordering it for lunch all the way from Singapadu to Denpasar, and despite the delivery cost being more expensive than the food itself üòÇ, it's absolutely worth every rupiah.

If you're on the way to Ubud or Kintamani through Singapadu, this warung near Bali Zoo is a perfect place to get a quick lunch. A small, comfortable spot overlooking the rice fields ‚Äì nothing fancy like Canggu's lunch bars, but the food beats their avocado toasts any day!
